                <h1>John Adams: The Legacy of Transparency in Governance</h1>
                <p>John Adams, the second President of the United States, was known for his commitment to transparency in governance. His dedication to open communication and ethical leadership helped set the foundation for future political norms. Adams emphasized the importance of honesty and integrity in public office, fostering trust between citizens and their leaders.</p>
